Package aloyslisp.commonlisp.common_lisp

Class Summary
fLOAD fLOAD [Function] load filename &key :verbose :print :if-does-not-exist :external-format This function loads the file named by filename into the Lisp environment.
fREAD fREAD [Function] read &optional input-stream eof-error-p eof-value recursive-p read reads in the printed representation of a Lisp object from input-stream, builds a corresponding Lisp object, and returns the object
fWRITE fWRITE [Function] write object &key :stream :escape :radix :base :circle :pretty :level :length :case :gensym :array :readably :right-margin :miser-width :lines :pprint-dispatch The printed representation of object is written to the output stream specified by :stream, which defaults to the value of *standard-output*.
